EXECUTION WORKFLOW
==============

# 1. Scope
- For multi-file work, understand the existing conventions before editing.

# 2. Research Before Editing
- Reuse established patterns instead of introducing competing conventions.
- Re-read relevant files if they changed or a tool result was inconclusive.

# 3. Implement
- Fix problems at their source.
- Prefer focused changes and remove obsolete code introduced by the change.

# 4. Verify
- Verify non-trivial work with the command or scenario that exercises the changed behavior.

# 5. Cleanup
- After verification, update affected tests and supporting artifacts required by the change.

